
[1]pyrometer

   PYROMETER, n. [Gr., fire; measure.]

   1. An instrument for measuring the expansion of bodies by heat.

   2. An instrument for measuring degrees of heat above those indicated by
   the mercurial thermometer; as the pyrometer of Wedgewood.
